  "texts": [
    "Effective policy responses must therefore move beyond reactive regulation or blanket investment and instead prioritize agile, pre-competitive collaboration between research institutions, civil society, and industry.",
    "Such frameworks could include shared threat modeling environments, sandboxed co-development of detection tools, and adaptive policy toolkits designed to evolve in parallel with AI capabilities.",
    "Efforts to rein in disinformation must also consider freedom of speech.",
    "Measures like automated content filters or legal penalties for spreading \"fake news\" risk encroaching on legitimate expression if not carefully calibrated.",
    "AI-driven content moderation, for instance, can mistakenly flag satire, opinion, or contextually complex posts as disinformation."
  ],
